4. The Deterministic Cost ModelThe overarching cost equation is a composite of flat-rate services, dimensional premiums, and indexed surcharges.$$C_{total} = C_{base} + P_{size} + S_{fuel} + C_{escort} + F_{penalty}$$A. Base Docking Cost ($C_{base}$)Billed as a flat-rate contractual fee per individual tugboat deployment.Multiplier: 1.0 (Standard), 1.5 (Shifting between berths).Holiday Premium: +35%.B. Vessel Size Premium ($P_{size}$)A flat fee applied exclusively if the vessel's Net Registered Tonnage (NRT) exceeds 40,000.
$$P_{size} = N_{tugs} \times \begin{cases} \$1,400, & \text{if } NRT > 40,000 \\ 0, & \text{otherwise} \end{cases}$$C. Fuel Surcharge Step Function ($S_{fuel}$)Uses a floor price of $2.00/gallon for Marine Ultra Low Sulfur Diesel (ULSD). Moran adds $15.00 per tug for every $0.10 increment (rounded UP) above the base.
$$S_{fuel} = N_{tugs} \times \left( \left\lceil \frac{Price_{fuel} - 2.00}{0.10} \right\rceil \times 15 \right)$$D. Spatial Cost Dynamics ($C_{escort}$)Hourly transit services are required for ULCVs and SLCVs.Two-Hour Minimum: All hourly services default to a 2.0-hour charge per tug.Zone Runtimes: NY/NJ is divided into geographic zones with fixed "Running Times" (e.g., 2.5 hours round-trip for Port Liberty).5. Operational AnomaliesThe "Absorbed Runtime" AnomalyIf a tugboat transitions immediately from an hourly escort into a flat-rate docking maneuver, the return travel time is absorbed by the docking fee. This prevents double-charging and can reduce billed time by up to 1.5 hours per tug.The "Escort Only" KVK TransitFor Kill Van Kull (KVK) transits, safety rules may require 3 tugs for transit but only 2 for the actual docking. The 3rd tug is billed as "Escort Only," meaning it does not trigger the flat-rate docking fee or the NRT size premium.6. Fleet Correlation AnalysisStatistical analysis of the Ocean Network Express (ONE) fleet confirms a near-perfect linear correlation between carrying capacity and tonnage.RelationshipCorrelation ScoreTEU vs. Gross Ton (GRT)0.988TEU vs. Net Ton (NRT)0.961Fleet-Specific Multipliers:$NRT = 1,253 + (5.12 \times TEU)$$GRT = 3,431 + (10.22 \times TEU)$7. Strategic DeploymentIntegrating this high-fidelity simulation into fleet management allows operators to:Optimize Scheduling: Chain dual services to exploit the "absorbed runtime" anomaly.Mitigate Surcharges: Predict if arrival windows fall into 35% holiday penalties or unfavorable tidal windows requiring extra tugs.Data-Driven Omission: Weigh hyper-localized harbor OPEX directly against the cost of deep-sea speeding.Developed for Moran New York Simulation Analysis
